# Guide: Adding a New Page to Your React App

This guide explains the design pattern and how to structure any new page following the same architecture.

---

## Architecture Overview

Your app follows a **component-based, CSS-separated architecture** with four layers:

| Layer | File | Purpose | Example |
|-------|------|---------|---------|
| **Generic UI** | `UIComponents.tsx` | Reusable, theme-agnostic components | Button, Input, Card, Heading |
| **Page Components** | `[PageName]Components.tsx` | Page-specific component compositions | LoginContainer, LoginHeader, LoginFormInputs |
| **Page Logic** | `[PageName].tsx` | State, logic, and component assembly | Form validation, API calls, navigation |
| **Page Styles** | `[PageName].css` | Page-specific CSS only | Layout, spacing, page-unique styling |

---

## Step-by-Step: Adding a New Page (Example: DashboardPage)

### Step 1: Create the Page Structure

Create these four files:

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── shared/
│   │   └── UIComponents.tsx
│   └── DashboardComponents.tsx          ← NEW
├── pages/
│   └── DashboardPage.tsx                ← NEW
├── styles/
│   ├── index.css
│   └── DashboardPage.css                ← NEW
└── contexts/
    ├── AuthContext.tsx
    └── ThemeContext.tsx
```

