## What Goes Where?

### 1️⃣ UIComponents.tsx (Generic, Reusable)

**Add to `UIComponents.tsx` ONLY if:**
- The component is **used on multiple pages**
- The component is **theme-aware** (uses CSS variables)
- The component is **self-contained** with no business logic

**Examples of what belongs here:**
```tsx
// ✅ YES - Generic and reusable
export const Button: React.FC<{ ... }> = ...
export const Input: React.FC<{ ... }> = ...
export const Card: React.FC<{ ... }> = ...
export const Container: React.FC<{ ... }> = ...

// ✅ YES - Theme-aware, no logic
export const ErrorMessage: React.FC<{ ... }> = ...
export const SuccessMessage: React.FC<{ ... }> = ...
```

**Examples of what does NOT belong here:**
```tsx
// ❌ NO - Page-specific composition
export const DashboardHeader = ...

// ❌ NO - Page-specific logic
export const UserStats = ...
```

---

### 2️⃣ DashboardComponents.tsx (Page-Specific Compositions)

**Add to `DashboardComponents.tsx` ONLY if:**
- The component is **composed of other components** (generic + custom)
- The component is **unique to this page**
- The component is **presentational** (no business logic, just props)
- The component wraps/structures page sections

**Examples of what belongs here:**

```tsx
// src/components/DashboardComponents.tsx
import React from 'react';
import { Container, Card, Heading, Text, Button } from './shared/UIComponents';

interface Colors {
  primary: string;
  text: string;
  // ... other colors
}

// ✅ Composition of generic components
export const DashboardContainer: React.FC<{ children: React.ReactNode }> = 
  ({ children }) => <Container className="dashboard-container">{children}</Container>;

// ✅ Composed section
export const DashboardHeader: React.FC<{ colors: Colors }> = 
  ({ colors }) => (
    <Card className="dashboard-header">
      <Heading level={1}>Welcome Back</Heading>
      <Text variant="secondary">Here's your dashboard overview</Text>
    </Card>
  );

// ✅ Composed stats section
export const StatsGrid: React.FC<{ 
  stats: Array<{ label: string; value: string | number }>;
  colors: Colors;
}> = ({ stats, colors }) => (
  <div className="stats-grid">
    {stats.map((stat) => (
      <Card key={stat.label} className="stat-card">
        <Text variant="secondary">{stat.label}</Text>
        <Heading level={3}>{stat.value}</Heading>
      </Card>
    ))}
  </div>
);

// ✅ Composed action buttons section
export const DashboardActions: React.FC<{ colors: Colors }> = 
  ({ colors }) => (
    <div className="dashboard-actions">
      <Button variant="primary">Create New</Button>
      <Button variant="secondary">Settings</Button>
      <Button variant="danger">Logout</Button>
    </div>
  );
```

**What these components do:**
- They **combine** generic UIComponents
- They **structure** the page layout
- They **accept props** (colors, data) but **no business logic**
- They are **purely presentational**

---

### 3️⃣ DashboardPage.tsx (Page Logic & Assembly)

**Add to `DashboardPage.tsx`:**
- **State management** (`useState`, `useReducer`)
- **Side effects** (`useEffect`)
- **Context hooks** (`useAuth`, `useTheme`)
- **Business logic** (validation, calculations, data fetching)
- **Event handlers** (clicks, form submissions)
- **Component assembly** (combining DashboardComponents)

**Example:**

```tsx
// src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useAuth } from '../contexts/AuthContext';
import { useTheme } from '../contexts/ThemeContext';
import {
  DashboardContainer,
  DashboardHeader,
  StatsGrid,
  DashboardActions,
} from '../components/DashboardComponents';

const DashboardPage: React.FC = () => {
  // ✅ State management
  const [stats, setStats] = useState<Array<{ label: string; value: number }>>([]);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  // ✅ Context hooks
  const { user, logout } = useAuth();
  const { colors, theme } = useTheme();

  // ✅ Business logic & side effects
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchDashboardStats();
  }, []);

  const fetchDashboardStats = async () => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    try {
      const response = await fetch('/api/dashboard/stats');
      const data = await response.json();
      setStats(data);
    } catch (err: any) {
      setError(err.message);
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };

  // ✅ Event handlers
  const handleLogout = () => {
    logout();
    // Navigate to login
  };

  const handleCreateNew = () => {
    // Navigate to create page
  };

  // ✅ Component assembly
  return (
    <DashboardContainer>
      <DashboardHeader colors={colors} />
      
      {isLoading && <p>Loading...</p>}
      {error && <p style={{ color: colors.error }}>{error}</p>}
      
      <StatsGrid stats={stats} colors={colors} />
      <DashboardActions colors={colors} />
    </DashboardContainer>
  );
};

export default DashboardPage;
```

